// Root Application Component
// Top-level React component wrapping the entire UI.
// Manages: theme, session selection, per-item auto-save, WebSocket subscription and message dispatch,
// history diff state, project/session CRUD, notification permission, and layout switching
// (desktop vs. mobile). Wrapped in ErrorBoundary and LoadingOverlay.

---

CLASS ErrorBoundary [private]
  React class component that catches render errors in its child tree.
  State: { hasError: boolean, error: Error | null }.
  getDerivedStateFromError: sets hasError=true and stores the error.
  componentDidCatch: logs error and errorInfo.
  render: IF hasError show a centered "Something went wrong" screen with a page-reload button.
          ELSE render children normally.

---

FUNCTION LoadingOverlay(show) [private]
  If show is false, render nothing.
  Else render a fullscreen semi-transparent overlay with a spinning indicator.

---

FUNCTION App()                                                          EXPORT
  CALLS: useIsMobile, useTheme, useUIStore, useSessionStore, useDataLoader, useAutoSave,
         useWebSocket, useSessionPolling, useQuestionStore, useChatStore,
         api.getUIState (App), api.createSession (App), api.archiveSession (App),
         api.deleteSession (App), requestNotificationPermission (notification-service),
         showUserInputNotification (notification-service), getWebSocketClient (websocket),
         generateSessionName (api)

  // --- State ---
  isMobile from useIsMobile.
  theme from useTheme.
  editMode, zoomLevel, zoom actions, chatPanelVisible, terminalPanelVisible from useUIStore.
  showSecondaryPanel = chatPanelVisible OR terminalPanelVisible.

  Full session state from useSessionStore: sessions, currentSession, setCurrentSession,
    diagrams, documents, designs, spreadsheets, snippets, todos, taskGraphSelected, todosSelected,
    todosProject, selectedTodo/Diagram/Document/Design/Spreadsheet/SnippetId,
    plus all add/update/remove actions and setPendingDiff, setCollabState.

  isLoading, dataError, loadSessions, loadSessionItems from useDataLoader.
  mermaidPreviewRef (imperative handle for center/fitToView).

  historyDiff: { timestamp, historicalContent, viewMode, compareMode, previousContent? } | null
  diagramHistoryPreview: { timestamp, historicalContent } | null
  designHistoryPreview: { timestamp, historicalContent } | null
  registeredProjects: string[]
  cleanupSession: Session | null
  isCleanupProcessing: boolean
  createSessionDialog: { project, suggestedName } | null
  localContent: string (mirrors selectedItem.content, updated by handleContentChange and useEffect)
  snippetToolbarControls: ReactNode (pushed up from SnippetEditor via onSnippetToolbarControls)

  currentQuestion, receiveQuestion from useQuestionStore.
  isConnected, isConnecting from useWebSocket.

  // --- On mount ---
  1. Call requestNotificationPermission (silently ignore failure).
  2. Call loadSessions and loadProjects.
  useSessionPolling on the current session's project+name every 5 seconds.

  // --- Session auto-select ---
  On first render when sessions are available and no currentSession: auto-select sessions[0].
  Only fires once (guarded by hasAutoSelectedRef).

  // --- Session items ---
  Whenever currentSession changes: call loadSessionItems(project, name).

  // --- Theme ---
  Apply/remove 'dark' class on documentElement when theme changes.

  // --- Page title ---
  Set document.title to "<project-leaf>/<session> - Mermaid Collab"; fallback to 'Mermaid Collab'.

  // --- WebSocket subscription ---
  When isConnected and currentSession: call client.subscribe('updates') and call restoreUIState.
  Subscribe to WebSocket messages. For each message, check project/session match then dispatch:

  diagram_updated       → updateDiagram(id, { content, lastModified })
  document_updated      → updateDocument; IF patchInfo present, also call setPendingDiff
  diagram_created       → addDiagram (only if project+session match)
  document_created      → addDocument (only if project+session match)
  diagram_deleted       → removeDiagram (only if project+session match)
  document_deleted      → removeDocument (only if project+session match)
  design_created        → addDesign
  design_updated        → updateDesign
  design_deleted        → removeDesign
  spreadsheet_created   → addSpreadsheet
  spreadsheet_updated   → updateSpreadsheet
  spreadsheet_deleted   → removeSpreadsheet
  snippet_created       → addSnippet
  snippet_updated       → updateSnippet
  snippet_deleted       → removeSnippet
  design_export_request → async: dynamically import designEditorRefs, renderNodesToImage, useDesignEditorStore;
                          call renderNodesToImage on the current page's children with the requested scale/format;
                          POST the binary result to /api/design-export-result/:requestId
  claude_question       → call receiveQuestion(question)
  ui_render             → call useChatStore.getState().addMessage; IF blocking, call showUserInputNotification
  session_state_updated → call setCollabState(state)
  session_created       → call loadSessions; IF no currentSession, auto-select the new session

  Unsubscribe from messages on cleanup.

  // --- restoreUIState ---
  If currentSession: call api.getUIState(project, name); if result is non-null,
  call useChatStore.getState().restoreUIFromCache with the cached state.

  // --- selectedItem ---
  Computed (useMemo) from the selected id across diagrams/documents/designs/spreadsheets/snippets.
  For snippets: try parsing content as JSON to extract groupName for display name.
  Returns null if nothing is selected.

  // --- effectiveContent ---
  useMemo that returns selectedItem.content (keyed on selectedItem.id and content).
  Used to prevent type mismatch when switching item types before localContent updates.

  // --- localContent sync ---
  useEffect: when selectedItem.id or content changes, update localContent.
  useEffect: when selectedItem.id changes, clear historyDiff, diagramHistoryPreview, designHistoryPreview.

  // --- Auto-save ---
  handleSave(content):
    1. Update the local store (updateDiagram/Document/Design/Spreadsheet).
    2. If WebSocket is connected, send update_diagram/update_document/update_design/update_spreadsheet/snippet_updated.
  useAutoSave(localContent, handleSave, 2000ms, selectedItem?.id).

  // --- History handlers ---
  handleHistoryVersionSelect(timestamp, content, previousContent):
    IF timestamp === 'current': clear historyDiff.
    ELSE: set historyDiff, preserving existing viewMode and compareMode.
  handleHistorySettingsChange(viewMode, compareMode): update historyDiff in-place.
  handleClearHistoryDiff: clear historyDiff.
  handleDiagramHistorySelect / handleDesignHistorySelect: set the respective preview state.
  handleDiagramRevert / handleDesignRevert: copy historicalContent into localContent, clear preview.

  // --- Project/session management ---
  loadProjects: GET /api/projects, extract project paths into registeredProjects.
  handleSessionSelect(session): call setCurrentSession.
  handleCreateSession(project): generate a session name, open the CreateSessionDialog.
  handleCreateSessionConfirm(name, type, useRenderUI): call api.createSession, reload sessions, select new session.
  handleAddProject: prompt user for a path; POST /api/projects; reload projects and sessions.
  handleRemoveProject(path): DELETE /api/projects?path=...; if current session belongs to it, clear it; reload.
  handleRefreshAll: reload projects, sessions, and current session items.
  handleDeleteSession(session): open the SessionCleanupDialog.
  handleCleanupAction(action):
    archive → api.archiveSession(project, name, { deleteSession: true, timestamp: false })
    delete  → api.deleteSession
    keep    → no-op
    archive-continue → api.archiveSession(project, name, { deleteSession: false, timestamp: true })
    After archive/delete: clear currentSession if it was the one cleaned up; reload sessions.

  // --- Toolbar overflow actions ---
  overflowActions (useMemo on selectedItem):
    Always: Copy (copy localContent to clipboard), Refresh (reload session items).
    Diagram: Format (disabled placeholder), Export Image (disabled placeholder).

  // --- renderMainContent ---
  IF isLoading: show spinner.
  IF dataError: show error message.
  IF todosSelected and no selectedTodoId: render TodosView.
  IF taskGraphSelected: render EditorToolbar (no save/undo) + TaskGraphView.
  ELSE: render EditorToolbar + UnifiedEditor with all history props threaded through.

  // --- Layout ---
  IF isMobile: render MobileLayout + QuestionPanel overlay + SessionCleanupDialog + CreateSessionDialog + ToastContainer, all inside ErrorBoundary.
  ELSE (desktop): render a flex-column full-screen layout:
    Header (session dropdown, project management, WS status)
    Flex row:
      Sidebar (fixed width)
      IF showSecondaryPanel: SplitPane(main | ChatPanel) with main containing renderMainContent()
      ELSE: plain main containing renderMainContent()
    QuestionPanel overlay (when currentQuestion is set)
    LoadingOverlay
    SessionCleanupDialog (when cleanupSession is set)
    CreateSessionDialog (when createSessionDialog is set)
    ToastContainer
  All inside ErrorBoundary.
